This is a new conversion in 1.4.1 to convert string to Date. It might fix your issue. <br />
<br />
I also would recommend you give 1.4.0 a try considering you are using version 1.0<br />
<br />
Jaimie<br />
<pre><code>  var stringToDate = function (s) {
        var b = s.split(/\D/);
        return new Date(Date.UTC(b[0], --b[1], b[2], b[3], b[4], b[5]));
    };</code></pre>
